		<div class="panel-heading">
  Shubh Aarambh Batch 2017 – 19 – MBA/PGDM School of Management 


            <b class="panel-title pull-right">July 17<sup>th</sup> 2017</b>
            <div style="clear:both"></div>
        </div>
		<div class="panel-body">
		

            <p align=justify><b>‘Shubh Aarambh’</b> marks the commencement of the academic year 2017-18 for the batch 2017-19, MBA/PGDM. It was conducted at 9:30 AM on 17/7/2017 at the Mini Auditorium, PG Block, Kristu Jayanti College. The programme was blessed with the presence of Rev. Fr. Josekutty P D, Principal, Kristu Jayanti College, Rev. Fr. Augustine George, Vice Principal, Kristu Jayanti College, Rev. Fr. Emmanuel P J, Faculty, Department of Psychology, Kristu Jayanti College, Dr. Aloysius Edward, DEAN, Faculty of Commerce & Management, Kristu Jayanti College and Dr. Vijaya Baskaran R, Head, Kristu Jayanti School of Management.</p>
            <p align=justify>The programme started with the invocation by the department choir followed by the welcome address by Dr. Aloysius Edward. Sir highlighted the objective of the MBA/PGDM programme in preparing the students not only to be successful corporate leaders but also to prepare them for their life. The Lamp lighting was done by our fathers, Dean, HOD, a student representative and a parent. The prayer session was led by the opening prayer by Rev. Fr. Augustine George. It was followed by the reading from the three Holy Scriptures the Bible, the Quran and the Rig Veda. This was followed by student’s prayer session with the concluding prayer by Rev. Fr. Emanuel P J. </p>
            <p align=justify>Rev Fr. Josekutty P D, delivered the presidential address. Quoting the example of Steve Jobs Co-founder of Apple Inc, Father made an appeal to students to think beyond their imagination in their journey of education with Kristu Jayanti School of Management. Father also presented the ‘3 R’s’ that form the backbone of a student’s success namely, ‘Resourcefulness through the facilities and knowledge provided through the course, Responsibility to fulfill the dreams of their parents and Respect everyone irrespective of anything’. Father also gave a mandate for the students to take the legacy of the Kristu Jayanti School of Management to the next level by actively participating and by owning the institution as from that day onwards they are part of the School of Management and the college.</p>
            <p>The programme ended with the college anthem followed by refreshments for the students and their parents & guardians. </p>


			
